    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Related code here:\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/HenryNguyen5/b1bcb3e9445e7efefb223015552ec429\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/HenryNguyen5/76a4896efc50aca32e8e42125ddad165\r\nThe node class has methods for getting/settings configurations for itself and network configs.\r\nAny JSON-RPC calls are put into a seperate file and then proxied into the node object.\r\nJSON-RPC calls are formulated as an object with:\r\n- Method and parameters\r\n- A post processor (What to do with the data after the node request returns)\r\n- An error handler (What to do if the node request fails)\r\n\r\nThis allows for easy composition of RPC-Methods with either default or customised post processors/error handlers.\r\n\r\nThe use of a proxy is used to avoid directly modifying `this` on the node class, keeping it clean of mutations in that sense.",
